					<description><![CDATA[<p>AI Cost Management Demand Drives New Funding PointFive announced it has raised $60 million of funding to gain more control of soaring cloud and AI expenditure. The company&#8217;s round was</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/pointfive-raises-60-million-expand-ai-efficiency-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">PointFive Raises $60 Million to Expand AI Efficiency Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>AI Cost Management Demand Drives New Funding</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">PointFive announced it has raised $60 million of funding to gain more control of soaring cloud and AI expenditure. The company&#8217;s round was led by Accel and saw participation from other venture capital firms including Index Ventures, Salesforce Ventures, Entre Capital, Perpetual Growth, Vesey Ventures and Sheva Ventures. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">New York-headquartered PointFive develops an AI and cloud efficiency platform that enables organisations to visualize, control and optimize infrastructure expenditure. The $60 million financing round, brings PointFive&#8217;s total amount raised to $96 million and will be used to further extend the platform capabilities and further growth abroad.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As AI adoption gains momentum rapidly, businesses are under more pressure as their infrastructure spending budgets become more unpredictable with large model deployment, higher compute usage, and increasingly large datasets. According to PointFive this represents a &#8220;major window of opportunity&#8221; for tools that offer insight into technology spend.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company also plans to increase its efforts in the United States and use the funding to expand on the product over AI services, cloud infrastructure and data platform, while more announcements related to their platform are expected in the next few weeks.</span></p>
<h2><b>Founders Build on Previous Startup Success</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">PointFive was created in 2023 by Alon Arvatz, Gal Ben-David and Amir Hozez. The three previously spent more than ten years together and were instrumental in the growth of the cybersecurity company IntSights. That business was acquired by Rapid7 in 2021 for $350m.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Their backgrounds in cybersecurity and enterprise software informed PointFive’s approach to infrastructure management. The founders realised that large organisations were struggling with the increasing complexity of cloud spending, with the rise of AI, that challenge was magnified with an expanded market for it.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company now has a team of over 100 staff across operations in Tel Aviv, London and the US, and a headcount that has continued to grow with the rising demand for automated cloud cost management tools, that identify waste, promote efficiency and eliminate overspend. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">The CEO Alon Arvatz said PointFive has moved on quite considerably since launch. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Though cost optimization of the cloud will continue, the focus of AI spending has now grown in importance. Many organisations are struggling to keep up with the pace. Arvatz said AI infrastructure spending is rising while vendors shift from subscriptions to consumption pricing.<br />
</span></p>
<h2><b>Enterprise Customers Seek Greater Visibility<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202571" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202571" class="size-full wp-image-202571" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-elem_sAnCdihgXHOTudeKNX4yBA_PGlOpsvfQWSLsAR4nJo6rQ.png" alt="AI platform optimizing cloud and infrastructure costs with real-time analysis and natural language insights." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202571" class="wp-caption-text">PointFive enables enterprises to monitor, understand, and optimize rising AI and. cloud infrastructure costs. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">PointFive&#8217;s platform functions as what the company describes as an AI Efficiency Operating System. The software continuously analyses cloud infrastructure, AI workloads, coding agents and data platforms. It then recommends actions that can improve operational efficiency and reduce costs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform aims to simplify complex financial data through natural language explanations. This allows engineering and finance teams to better understand where resources are being consumed. Organisations can then make more informed decisions about infrastructure investments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Several large enterprises already use the platform. Customers include Nubank, E.ON, Hertz, Fanatics, Swiss Post and NICE. These organisations operate large technology environments where even small efficiency improvements can generate meaningful savings.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to the company, some customers have achieved positive returns shortly after deployment. Nubank reportedly reached a positive return on </span><a href="https://www.investopedia.com/terms/i/investment.asp" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">investment</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> within ten days of implementing the platform. Such results have helped strengthen PointFive&#8217;s position in a competitive software market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Interest in AI cost management continues to grow across industries. Businesses are deploying generative AI tools at scale, often without fully understanding long-term spending implications. This creates demand for platforms that can monitor usage patterns and recommend optimisation opportunities before costs escalate.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/hunter-point-capital-raises-4-3-billion-gp-financing-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Hunter Point Capital Raises $4.3 Billion to Expand GP Financing Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Investors Bet on the Future of AI Infrastructure</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series B round reflects growing investor interest in companies supporting AI adoption rather than building foundation models directly. As organisations increase AI usage, supporting infrastructure providers are becoming important parts of the broader ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Accel led the financing alongside a group of venture firms with strong enterprise technology portfolios. The participation of existing investors suggests continued confidence in PointFive&#8217;s execution and market position. Has grown very rapidly since its founding and it is still securing new and large enterprise customers. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Analysts forecast that spending on AI infrastructure will continue to remain a key area of focus for businesses globally. Many are at the very beginning of the adoption lifecycle and they will be much more concerned with costs and operational efficiency as usage increases.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">PointFive intends to invest heavily in product innovation following the raise. The company wants to increase coverage across production AI services and cloud environments. It also plans to strengthen capabilities that help enterprises manage spending linked to coding agents and automated development tools.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400"> The total market is still growing. Businesses are trying to get insight into their increasingly complicated tech stacks and solutions that merge financial insight and actionable advice could be very important as AI becomes commonplace across enterprises.PointFive now has the capital to capitalize on this. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They are poised for their next wave of growth with new money and a growing customer base that wants more AI efficiency. The investors in this round believe managing AI spend will be just as important as actually using AI.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
