					<description><![CDATA[<p>Galvany has successfully closed a €10 million seed funding round. This new injection of capital coincides with the period of hypergrowth the company is experiencing, and during which GALVANY is</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/galvany-raises-e10m-to-accelerate-energy-transition/" data-wpel-link="internal">GALVANY Raises €10M to Accelerate Energy Transition</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://ventureburn.com/pathway-power-secures-150m-for-battery-storage-expansion/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Galvany </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has successfully closed a €10 million seed </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/pathway-power-secures-150m-for-battery-storage-expansion/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. This new injection of capital coincides with the period of hypergrowth the company is experiencing, and during which GALVANY is changing the industry of residential heating by evolving heat pumps from simple appliances to real active and intelligent players of the European power grid.</span></p>
<p>SET Ventures, an Amsterdam-based energy tech fund, and Berlin&#8217;s AENU climate fund co-led the funding round. Institutional supporters increasingly agree that software, rather than equipment manufacturing, should determine the next major step in the global energy transition.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the Fragmentation of the Heat-Pump Market</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2022 by Raik Belka, GALVANY was established to fix Germany&#8217;s highly fragmented, bureaucratic heating transition. On paper, Europe has an abundant supply of clean heating systems. In practice, residential property owners face a frustrating journey split across disconnected silos, navigating maze-like government subsidy applications, finding available local technicians for installation, and manually coordinating different hardware systems.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202541" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202541" class="size-large wp-image-202541" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Heating-system-1024x768.jpg" alt="Heating system" width="1024" height="768" /><p id="caption-attachment-202541" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">GALVANY bridges this gap by acting as a fully integrated end-to-end platform. The company bundles consulting, upfront financial sales, government subsidy handling, and physical installation through its nationwide network into a singular, transparent customer workflow. To date, the company has successfully deployed more than 2,500 integrated systems across Germany.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;In Germany, heat pumps do not fail because of the technology itself but because of the vast gap between complex subsidy bureaucracy, localised installation capacity, and end-consumer affordability,&#8221; explained Raik Belka, founder and CEO of GALVANY. &#8220;We built the technical and physical infrastructure to make the transition painless and financially viable from day one.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/pathway-power-secures-150m-for-battery-storage-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Pathway Power Secures $150M for Battery Storage Expansion</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The First Heating System That Pays for Itself</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">At the technical core of GALVANY&#8217;s offering is a modular hardware-software ecosystem. The company distributes the GALVANY Cube, a hardware configuration developed in a strategic manufacturing partnership with industrial giant Panasonic. The system combines a high-efficiency heat pump with modular home battery storage and smart metering infrastructure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The entire apparatus is governed by GALVANY Fusion, an AI-powered &#8220;Agentic Energy Operating System&#8221;. Rather than running a static heating schedule, the software constantly communicates with external energy markets. It tracks real-time price fluctuations on the wholesale day-ahead and intraday electricity markets, alongside dynamic regional tariffs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The AI autonomously executes automated load shifting: it charges home batteries and preheats residential spaces when renewable energy is flooding the grid, and power prices are low (or occasionally negative). Conversely, it curtails grid consumption during peak hours, drawing instead from stored battery power. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By shifting energy demand dynamically based on market signals, the platform dramatically lowers household utilities, delivering on the company’s consumer promise of &#8220;the first heating system that pays for itself&#8221;.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Expansion into Multifamily Buildings</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With the €10 million capital stack secured, GALVANY has detailed a clear roadmap for country-wide scaling. A primary operational focus will be expanding its platform architecture into the multifamily residential housing sector. </span>Urban Europe considers existing apartment complexes the most carbon-heavy and traditionally difficult-to-electrify properties. Engineering teams will release the first consumer-facing GALVANY mobile app in summer 2026, giving homeowners visibility over real-time grid arbitrage savings and carbon reductions.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;GALVANY is one of the rare European companies that cleanly connects the consumer&#8217;s household device all the way out to the regional power grid,&#8221; noted Dr. Till Stenzel, Partner at SET Ventures. &#8220;With its integrated platform and sophisticated energy management software, the residential heat pump evolves from a simple appliance into a core, flexible asset for a digitally controlled energy network.&#8221;</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/galvany-raises-e10m-to-accelerate-energy-transition/" data-wpel-link="internal">GALVANY Raises €10M to Accelerate Energy Transition</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
