					<description><![CDATA[<p>Blnk Secures New Capital to Accelerate Growth Blnk, a digital consumer finance platform, has raised $12.5M in Series A funding. Algebra Ventures led the round which also included participation from</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/blnk-raises-12-5m-series-a-consumer-finance-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Blnk Raises $12.5M Series A to Expand Consumer Finance Across MENA</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Blnk Secures New Capital to Accelerate Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Blnk, a digital consumer finance platform, has raised $12.5M in Series A funding. Algebra Ventures led the round which also included participation from SANAD Fund for MSME, Endeavor Catalyst, and Emirates International Investment Company.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Egyptian fintech provider also received a further $24.6M in debt financing from facilities provided by Suez Canal Bank, Bank Albaraka, National Bank of Egypt, along with various non-bank financial institutions (NBFIs). The total equity and debt funding combined reached $37.1M.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company, which was founded in 2021, aims to make consumer finance available across the Middle East and North Africa and enables </span><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/merchant" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">merchants</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> to provide point-of-sale (POS) financing at checkout while customers receive credit decisions within minutes via a digital interface.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;This funding is testament to the immense belief in Blnk&#8217;s vision,&#8221; CEO Amr Sultan commented. &#8220;The investment will significantly allow us to increase our reach and improve our profitability as well as make financial services more accessible to underserviced customers.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding comes at a time of rapid growth for the consumer finance sector within Egypt and an increasing demand for alternative lending products, as fintech services are stepping up to fill gaps left by conventional banks.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Technology Powers Instant Credit Decisions</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Blnk uses machine learning and AI to facilitate a faster and simpler financing application process, which customers can complete in three minutes. Minimal paperwork and a streamlined, in-store application process are key to Blnk&#8217;s offering.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Blnk enables its consumers to borrow for 6–36 months and employs proprietary underwriting algorithms for instant risk analysis, to allow more accelerated underwriting and faster financing decisions.  Machine learning models calculate likelihood of default to enable variable pricing, unlike standard loan decisions which are usually made based solely on credit checks alone. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Blnk&#8217;s application will leverage both local behavioural and financial data to enhance risk assessments beyond credit history alone, expanding access to credit for previously excluded customer segments, and ultimately closing lending gaps across developing economies with the use of technology.</span></p>
<h2><b>Financial Inclusion Remains a Major Opportunity<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202543" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202543" class="size-full wp-image-202543" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-with_0o_BTZ7OXWS2QD6iM6MSig_mBwnR3ntQ2SwFLVjZJpbTA_cover.png" alt="Digital consumer finance platform expanding credit access to underserved populations with AI-driven lending systems" width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202543" class="wp-caption-text">Blnk expands financial inclusion in Egypt by bringing digital credit access to underserved and previously unbanked populations. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Egypt’s consumer finance market has expanded rapidly in recent years. Industry data shows the sector reached approximately EGP 96.3 billion in 2025. That represented growth of more than 57 percent compared with the previous year.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Despite this expansion, access to formal credit remains limited. Fewer than five percent of adults are estimated to have access to formal lending products. The gap is even wider among female consumers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Only a small percentage of women currently use credit cards or online lending services. This highlights the disconnect between financial inclusion efforts and actual access to credit. Blnk is targeting these underserved segments through its platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company reports that around 75 percent of its users were previously unbanked or underserved. More than 35 percent of customers are women. These figures demonstrate the company’s focus on expanding participation in formal financial services.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Since its seed round in 2022, Blnk has onboarded more than one million customers. Its loan portfolio has grown beyond EGP 1 billion. The company also achieved profitability in 2025 following strong revenue growth.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/cresco-labs-secures-us50-million-credit-facility/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Cresco Labs Secures US$50 Million Credit Facility to Fund Growth Strategy</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Credit Card Launch and Regional Expansion Plans</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In order to advance its infrastructure capabilities, Blnk will invest its new capital into technology. Blnk is also going to implement new financing products and currently exploring new geographical expansions. Financial inclusion remains important for governments, investors and regulators alike, and Blnk is poised with equity and significant debt facilities for its next phase.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most critical of these is Blnk&#8217;s introduction of a credit card product, where customers can access their credit limits in merchants not operating within Blnk&#8217;s currently expanding network, and thereby providing customers with increased buying freedom. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Blnk is currently working with over 3,000 merchants with service locations ranging from electronics and furniture shops, through to appliances and automotive repair services. If the credit card system is implemented as envisioned, it may offer access to financed purchases to an audience much further than currently exists. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In management&#8217;s eyes, the creation of more versatile products will not only increase customer loyalty but could also provide further revenue sources to spur future growth. Despite Blnk&#8217;s current place within the highly competitive fintech industry, digital loan solutions are seeing increasing demand throughout the region. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/blnk-raises-12-5m-series-a-consumer-finance-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Blnk Raises $12.5M Series A to Expand Consumer Finance Across MENA</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
